<h2 class="center">Chapter 1</h2>
<h2 class="center">Introduction</h2>

<h3>1.1 Introduction</h3>
<p>The Smart Home Services Management System connects households with local service workers like electricians, plumbers, and painters. Our system guarantees safety by verifying every worker's ID documents and tracking jobs from start to finish. We have built this app to have the exact same features on both the Web Application (which is fully completed) and the Mobile Application (which is just in its final few steps). Therefore, when we mention Resident and Provider features, they are available on both the website and the mobile phone.</p>
<p>Smart Home Services Management System is divided into three main parts:</p>
<ul>
    <li><b>Admin (Web Dashboard)</b></li>
    <li><b>Resident (Web Site & Mobile App)</b></li>
    <li><b>Service Provider (Web Site & Mobile App)</b></li>
</ul>

<p><b>Admin Features:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Admins can log into a Web Dashboard to see total earnings and user graphs.</li>
<li>Admins can add, edit, or delete Service Categories like "Plumbing" or "Cleaning".</li>
<li>Admins check and verify Service Providers by looking at their real CNIC pictures (KYC Approval).</li>
<li>Admins manage platform commissions and money in the wallets.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>User (Resident) & Provider Features:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Both users sign up using an OTP check for security.</li>
<li>Residents can mark their exact home address on a GPS Map when asking for a service.</li>
<li>Providers can view nearby "Available Jobs" and send a price offer back to the Resident.</li>
<li>Both users can talk in a built-in Live Chat where they can send text, pictures, or videos.</li>
<li>The job has a safe step-by-step design: It goes from 'Requested' tracking, to 'Working', and then 'Completed' using an OTP code given to the provider to confirm the work is done.</li>
</ul>

<h3>1.2 Objectives of the Project</h3>
<ul>
<li>To create trust between people and online home service workers using secure ID verification (KYC).</li>
<li>To build a fast and easy-to-use Web and Mobile App.</li>
<li>To offer real-time live chat so users don't have to make phone calls.</li>
<li>To save time for people who normally have to go outside to find physical workers.</li>
<li>To create a safe and fair payment system with a platform wallet.</li>
</ul>

<h3>1.3 Organization of the Project</h3>
<p>This project uses modern web programming tools to work. The Web Application is fast and changes dynamically without needing the page to reload every time. We used a NoSQL database, which makes storing different types of data very simple. The same database and server connect the React Web Application and the React Native Mobile Application at the same time.</p>

<h3>1.4 Programming Languages</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>JavaScript</b> is the main language used.</li>
<li><b>Node.js and Express</b> are used for the backend server.</li>
<li><b>React.js</b> is used for the Resident, Provider, and Admin Web pages.</li>
<li><b>React Native</b> is used for building the Mobile App.</li>
<li><b>MongoDB</b> is used as the database to store our records.</li>
<li><b>Socket.io</b> is used to make the chat messages appear instantly.</li>
</ul>

<h3>1.5 Background of Project</h3>
<p>We saw that when a pipe breaks or a fan stops working at home, finding a reliable worker is very hard and unsafe. People have to ask neighbors or go to a market to find someone. Our platform solves this by bringing workers directly to the mobile phone or computer. All workers are checked by the Admin, and prices are agreed upon before the worker starts.</p>

<h3>1.6 Operational Environment</h3>
<p><b>Mobile Phones:</b> Any modern Android phone or iPhone.<br/>
<b>Web Browser:</b> Google Chrome, Safari, Firefox, etc.<br/>
<b>DATABASE:</b> MongoDB Cloud.<br/>
<b>SERVER:</b> Node.js Server Environment.</p>

<h3>1.7 Advantages</h3>
<ul>
<li>Finding a worker is very fast and can be done from a mobile phone or laptop.</li>
<li>Safety is high because the Admin checks the Provider's real ID card first.</li>
<li>Using the GPS map means the worker will not get lost finding the house.</li>
<li>Live chat makes it easy to share pictures of the broken item before the worker arrives.</li>
</ul>

<h3>1.8 Disadvantages</h3>
<ul>
<li>It requires a good internet connection from both the Resident and the Provider for the app to update the live locations and chat.</li>
<li>Users need some basic knowledge of how to use smartphones or websites to book a job.</li>
</ul>

<div class="page-break"></div>

<h2 class="center">Chapter 2</h2>
<h2 class="center">System Analysis</h2>

<h3>2.1 Software Requirement Specification</h3>
<h4>2.1.1 General Description</h4>
<p><b>Problem Statement:</b><br/>
Right now, the home service industry is very disorganized. People face problems finding good plumbers or electricians quickly. Customers have trust issues because they don't know who is coming into their homes. Workers also want an easy way to find nearby jobs without waiting in markets. We need an application that is available on Web and Mobile, allowing customers to book services safely by tracking the location and checking identities.</p>

<h4>2.1.2 System Objectives</h4>
<ul>
<li>To save the effort needed to physically search for workers.</li>
<li>To provide a live chat so users can explain their problems clearly.</li>
<li>To organize jobs clearly, showing their status (Pending, Working, Completed).</li>
</ul>

<h4>2.1.3 System Requirements</h4>
<h5>2.1.3.1 Functional Requirements</h5>
<table>
<tr><th>No</th><th>Requirements</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR1</td><td>User Registration</td><td>A user can make an account by providing an Email and Password. They verify it using an OTP code sent to their email.</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR2</td><td>User Login</td><td>The user enters their email and password to safely log into their Web or Mobile dashboard.</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR3</td><td>Admin Verification (KYC)</td><td>Service Providers upload pictures of their ID cards. The Admin looks at these and clicks "Approve" or "Reject".</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR4</td><td>Post a Job (With GPS)</td><td>Residents enter test details and pick their exact house location on a live GPS map to post a job request.</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR5</td><td>Provider Offers Price</td><td>Providers see the job on their screen and can send back a price they want to charge.</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR6</td><td>Live Socket Chat</td><td>Resident and Provider can instantly message each other or send pictures without reloading the page.</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR7</td><td>Status & OTP Verification</td><td>When finishing the job, the Provider changes the status to "Completed", and the Resident gives them an OTP code to verify it.</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR8</td><td>Manage Wallet</td><td>Providers can view their wallet balance and see the platform commissions deducted from their earnings.</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR9</td><td>Submit Reviews</td><td>Residents can give a star rating and write a review about the service provider after the job is finished.</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR10</td><td>View Notifications</td><td>Users receive instant notifications for new messages, offers, and job status changes.</td></tr>
</table>

<h5>2.1.3.2 Non-Functional Requirements</h5>
<table>
<tr><th>No</th><th>Requirements</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>NFR1</td><td>Performance</td><td>The app must load fast. When someone sends a message, it should show up instantly.</td></tr>
<tr><td>NFR2</td><td>Reliability</td><td>The system should not crash or lose important job data.</td></tr>
<tr><td>NFR3</td><td>Usability</td><td>The Web site and Mobile App should be very simple, so anyone can use it without confusion.</td></tr>
<tr><td>NFR4</td><td>Security</td><td>Passwords must be hidden and users must log in safely using secure tokens (JWT).</td></tr>
</table>

<h4>2.1.4 Software and Hardware Requirements</h4>
<h5>2.1.4.1 Software Requirements</h5>
<ul>
<li>Operating System: Works on Windows, Android, and iOS.</li>
<li>Editor: Visual Studio Code.</li>
<li>Frontend Languages: React JS (For Web) and React Native (For Mobile).</li>
<li>Backend Languages: Node.js and Express.</li>
<li>Database: MongoDB.</li>
</ul>

<h5>2.1.4.2 Hardware Requirements</h5>
<ul>
<li>A laptop for development.</li>
<li>A smartphone with an internet connection and GPS location services turned on.</li>
</ul>

