<h2 class="center">Chapter 5</h2>
<h2 class="center">Backend Database and Server Cloud</h2>
<p><i>Our project uses a modern custom server instead of Firebase.</i></p>

<h3>5.1 Node.js & Express API</h3>
<p>The brain of the system is built with Node.js. Express is used to create simple rules (APIs) so the Web App and Mobile App can easily talk to the database securely.</p>
<div class="figure-placeholder">
  [ Insert Figure 5.1 Here: Logo of Node.js ]
</div>

<h3>5.2 JWT Authentication</h3>
<p>To make logging in very safe, we use JWT (JSON Web Tokens). When a user logs in, the server gives them a secret digital key. The Web or Mobile app uses this key to prove it is the real user without sending the password again.</p>
<div class="figure-placeholder">
  [ Insert Figure 5.2 Here: Diagram of JWT Token flow ]
</div>

<h3>5.3 MongoDB Database</h3>
<p>MongoDB is our online storage. MongoDB is flexible and fast. It stores complex information like GPS coordinates, user profile details, chat histories, and ID image links perfectly.</p>
<div class="figure-placeholder">
  [ Insert Figure 5.3 Here: MongoDB Cloud Dashboard ]
</div>

<h3>5.4 Live Socket Chat</h3>
<p>We use Socket.io to allow the Resident and Provider to talk instantly without refreshing their screens. It makes the chat feel alive, just like normal chatting apps.</p>

<div class="page-break"></div>

