</tr>
</table>

<p><b>Test Case ID: 02</b><br/>
<b>Test Case Name:</b> Post a Job Request<br/>
<b>Test Priority:</b> High<br/>
<b>Preconditions:</b> Resident is logged in and selects a location on the map.</p>
<table border="1">
<tr><th>SN</th><th>Action Inputs</th><th>Expected Outcome</th><th>Actual Outcome</th><th>Test Result</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>1.</td><td>Category: Cleaning<br/>Location: Selected<br/>Description: "Clean my fan"</td><td>Job is created and nearby Providers get a new job notification.</td><td>Job created successfully.</td><td>Pass</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>2.</td><td>Category: Left Blank<br/>Location: Selected</td><td>System tells the user "Please select a category".</td><td>Error displayed prohibiting blank job.</td><td>Pass</td>
</tr>
</table>

<p><b>Test Case ID: 03</b><br/>
<b>Test Case Name:</b> Admin Accept KYC Document<br/>
<b>Test Priority:</b> High<br/>
<b>Preconditions:</b> Provider uploaded images. Admin is logged in to Dashboard.</p>
<table border="1">
<tr><th>SN</th><th>Action Inputs</th><th>Expected Outcome</th><th>Actual Outcome</th><th>Test Result</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>1.</td><td>Admin clicks "Approve" button on pending Provider.</td><td>Provider status changes to Approved and Provider can now see available jobs.</td><td>Status updated beautifully.</td><td>Pass</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h3>6.2 Test Case Specifications</h3>

<h4>6.2.1 Black Box Testing</h4>
<p>We tested the system functionality like normal users. For example, we clicked the "Send Message" button in the chat on the Web, and checked if it appeared instantly on the Mobile phone screen without looking at the backend code.</p>

<h4>6.2.2 White Box Testing</h4>
<p>We looked precisely at the code. We checked if the math formulas inside our backend successfully subtracted the correct platform commission percentage from the provider's wallet balance when a job was finished.</p>

<div class="page-break"></div>

<h2 class="center">Chapter 7</h2>
<h2 class="center">Conclusion</h2>

<h3>7.1 Conclusion</h3>
<p>The Smart Home Services Management System provides an incredibly easy and safe way for households to find technical workers directly from their laptops or mobile phones. It solves the problem of finding trustworthy people because every worker's ID is checked by an Admin. The platform is built using very fast and popular tools like React JS for the Web and React Native for the Mobile Application, connected together by Node.js and MongoDB. The system successfully provides GPS tracking and a live chat to make the user experience amazing.</p>

<h3>7.2 Future Work</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Adding Real Payment Methods:</b> We plan to integrate easy popular payment systems directly into the app, such as <b>EasyPaisa, JazzCash, and SadaPay</b>. This makes it so users can pay for services directly from their digital wallets easily without needing hard cash.</li>
<li><b>AI Photo Helper:</b> Letting users upload a picture of a broken pipe so that the app can auto-guess the problem and recommend a price instantly.</li>
<li><b>Live Movement Tracking:</b> Adding a feature so the user can see a tiny car icon moving on the map when the Provider is driving to their house.</li>
</ul>

